4 workers work 8 hours per day for 5 days.
Total units of work = 4 Ã— 8 Ã— 5 = 160 4Ã—8Ã—5=160 units.
When the work is doubled: New total units of work = 160 Ã— 2 = 320 160Ã—2=320 units.
Let ð‘¥ x be the number of hours taken by 2 men to complete the work in 20 days: Total units of work done by 2 men in ð‘¥ x hours per day for 20 days = 2 Ã— 20 Ã— ð‘¥ 2Ã—20Ã—x.
